    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nCurrently, setting `conceallevel` conceals all characters in the viewable portion of the buffer, except for the line that the cursor is on. For example:\r\n![image](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/48545987/19aca50a-2082-4736-8620-89a39ec0ebd0)\r\nThere exists the `concealcursor` option, but enabling that makes it so the *entire line* gets concealed, e.g.\r\n![image](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/48545987/766bacfc-54b4-4381-9aec-5327b556011b)\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nIt would be nice to have some way to only un-conceal text under the cursor, to have the benefits of reading the surrounding context while also being able to edit. Some examples created using [this plugin](https://github.com/jishnusen/nvim-inline-surround/) (the main focus being on the `\\cong` and `\\times`):\r\n![image](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/48545987/5947ae1e-22b8-4400-b7b4-3b1133726f1c)\r\n![image](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/48545987/9b9f4e19-c108-46cb-85f4-6d6c26ba67b5)",
    "closed_at": null,
